105	pehve1ns2liorik06ad22my5	11 Dec 2023: CSE Group Featured on the Teaching Matters Blog	Following a successful launch event and the doubling of our group's membership list with members from Computer Science/Informatics schools and beyond,  we concluded that  there is wide scope for our group's activities. Therefore, we proceeded with promoting the group more widely within the University of Edinburgh, by publishing a blog post in the Teaching Matters Blog. This blog post introduces the CSE Group and what sets it apart, describes our activities so far and plans for the future, and encourages readers to join us. \n\nYou can read the blog here:\n\nhttps://www.teaching-matters-blog.ed.ac.uk/launching-the-computer-science-education-group-fostering-collaboration-and-advancement/	2026-07-11 15:19:45.408	2026-07-11 15:19:55.174	\N	\N	3	\N	test1	sam_jia97@126.com	approved	We are thrilled to announce a new blog post, this time in Teaching Matters, the University of Edinburgh's platform for teaching discussions!	I'm here	\N
