4	q5pua18p5vvlyr84oasrlvav	Emails use <%= variable %> for substuition and aim to follow the underlying api variable names (not user friendly labels) e.g. eventType. \n\nThese variable names are found in Content type buidler > Edit (top right)\n\nThe variable can be <%= variableFormatted %> indicating the variable is modified before being inserted instead of using the raw value\n\nThis is inspired by Strapi's email formatting. Though strapi uses HTML\n[https://docs.strapi.io/cms/features/users-permissions#templating-emails](https://docs.strapi.io/cms/features/users-permissions#templating-emails)\n\n[https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.23#template](https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.23#template)	2026-01-29 19:36:05.102	2026-01-29 19:36:05.102	2026-01-29 19:36:05.098	1	1	\N	Using email templates
5	pkryz2g3hq4qmhcbjig97hw1	This describes how to automatically generate reminder emails from templates and sending them on a schedule\n\n1. Fill in event title, speaker, location, date and time\n2. Click `Generate emails` button at the bottom\n3. The system will generate 3 emails with default times set to 7 days before, 3 days before and on the date of the event itself\n4. You can disable some reminder emails by **toggling the switch then saving the draft**\n5. Whenever you click save draft, it will update the scheduled emails.	2026-01-29 19:59:07.687	2026-01-29 19:59:07.687	2026-01-29 19:59:07.682	1	1	\N	Sending email documentation
3	gprskf4rmcwx3fgzfaah77l2	To use the editor\n1. Click `Expand` in bottom right to see markdown and rendered text side by side\n2. Use the below template to be familiar with markdown's features\n```\n# Markdown Template - heading 1\n## Heading 2\n### Heading 3\n#### Heading 4\n\nLists (blue icons in [1])\n1. item 1\n2. item 2\n- item 3\n- item 4\n\nText is **bold**, _italics_ and <u>underlined</u>. Select text and click\none of the icons annotated in Red in [1]\n\nLinks\n1. Write link\n2. Highlight link\n3. Click Link Button (yellow annotated icon). IMPORTANT: both [] and () must have same text. \n\n[https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/#links](https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/#links)\n\nImage\n1. Click image button\n2. Select correct folder\n3. Click 'Add more assets' (top right)\n4. Drag and drop or click plus sign\n5. Click 'Upload 1 asset to library' (bottom right)\n6. Close the Media button to refresh it\n7. Navigate to target image and click the checkbox on the image \n8. Click 'Finish' (bottom right)\n![markdownbar2.png](http://localhost:1337/uploads/markdownbar2_8eebcf478a.png)\n\nFeel free to copy and paste this template\n```\n[1]\n![markdownbar2.png](http://localhost:1337/uploads/markdownbar2_8eebcf478a.png)\n![markdownbar2.png](https://wise-wealth-46b9441c98.strapiapp.com/7/uploads/markdownbar2_8eebcf478a.png)\n\n[2] Learn more\n[https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/#links](https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/#links)	2026-01-28 00:30:21.756	2026-02-02 09:58:32.015	2026-02-02 09:58:32.002	1	1	\N	Standard markdown template
