611	owjt6wr5wr70eqgoix5zdq6i	TeachAThon 2025 Closing Event,	2025-10-27	Informatics Forum G.03 (in person),	Dr. Pavlos Andreadis	2026-01-30 16:45:22.618	2026-01-31 19:02:22.301	\N	1	1	\N	14:00:00	16:00:00	t	0	\N	Other	# What is TeachAThon? \nTeachAThon is a new hackathon where students got a chance to design and prototype GenAI solutions for higher education. \n\n## What will be presented? \nWe have received a wide range of submissions including tutors, lecture assistants, and study guides. Shortlisted submissions will be presented on the day.\n\n鈮∑捗喢?There will be over **鈹?500 in prizes** for the winning teams, provided by the GenAI Integration in CS Education project, itself generously funded by the University of Edinburgh Principal螕脟脰s Teaching Award Scheme (PTAS). \nThe most innovative, useful, ethical, and well-thought-out projects will be recognised. \n\nDon螕脟脰t miss this chance to see what students have come up with, and to explore how GenAI can help transform our education!\n\nHope to see you there,\nPavlos.\n\n1. Item 1\n2. Item 2\n\n- Item 1\n- Item 2\n\nAI & Storytelling [https://aist.cortu01.com/](https://aist.cortu01.com/)	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	t	t	\N	https://google.com	Abstract	t	Hybrid event (online and in-person)	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
649	owjt6wr5wr70eqgoix5zdq6i	TeachAThon 2025 Closing Event,	2025-10-27	Informatics Forum G.03 (in person),	Dr. Pavlos Andreadis	2026-01-30 16:45:22.618	2026-01-31 19:02:22.301	2026-01-31 19:02:22.329	1	1	\N	14:00:00	16:00:00	t	0	\N	Other	# What is TeachAThon? \nTeachAThon is a new hackathon where students got a chance to design and prototype GenAI solutions for higher education. \n\n## What will be presented? \nWe have received a wide range of submissions including tutors, lecture assistants, and study guides. Shortlisted submissions will be presented on the day.\n\n鈮∑捗喢?There will be over **鈹?500 in prizes** for the winning teams, provided by the GenAI Integration in CS Education project, itself generously funded by the University of Edinburgh Principal螕脟脰s Teaching Award Scheme (PTAS). \nThe most innovative, useful, ethical, and well-thought-out projects will be recognised. \n\nDon螕脟脰t miss this chance to see what students have come up with, and to explore how GenAI can help transform our education!\n\nHope to see you there,\nPavlos.\n\n1. Item 1\n2. Item 2\n\n- Item 1\n- Item 2\n\nAI & Storytelling [https://aist.cortu01.com/](https://aist.cortu01.com/)	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	t	t	\N	https://google.com	Abstract	t	Hybrid event (online and in-person)	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
650	qqok63fiu9vi2iy4l7d8x5k6	What I learned at the UK Conference on Teaching Statistics 2025, and the talk I gave there: Assessment of Critical Evaluation in the age of LLMs	2026-03-05	Robertson's close	Dr. David Sterratt, who is a Lecturer and the Deputy Director of Teaching (Operations) in the University of Edinburgh School of Informatics	2026-01-30 16:47:49.046	2026-01-31 19:03:13.107	2026-01-31 19:03:13.163	1	1	\N	10:00:00	16:00:00	f	0	\N	Teaching Hour	# Assessing Critical Evaluation of Data Science Studies in the age of\nLLMs\n\nUntil 2024, we assessed a learning outcome of critically evaluating\ndata-driven methods and claims from case studies via a coursework in\nwhich students answered a set of questions at various levels on Bloom's\ntaxonomy about a data science study, typically a short scientific\narticle, and an accompanying media article. We believed, and students\nreported, that examining how statistical concepts are used in a real\nstudy and how they are reported in the media was a valuable experience.\nLarge language models can now do the task well enough to get a more\nthan passing grade. It is not currently possible to detect LLM-\ngenerated text with enough certainty to count as academic misconduct,\nand although the <u>LLM-generated work has flaws, it is time-consuming for\nmarkers to identify them</u>. We are therefore attempting to assess\ncritical evaluation in an exam, while still retaining the experience of\nengaging with an authentic study. Our general approach is to introduce\na study to students throughout the semester, and write exam questions\nrelated to the study. This talk will describe our approach and evaluate\nhow well it has worked this year.\n\nWe hope to see you then!\nKind regards,\n	\N	\N	Teaching Hour - Thursday 5th Mar, 12am - What I learned at the UK Conference on Teaching Statistics 2025, and the talk I gave there: Assessment of Critical Evaluation in the age of LLMs	Dear all,\n\nThis is a reminder for the next Computer Science Education Group Teaching Hour on Thursday 5th March at 10:00-16:00. This event will be in person in Robertson's close\n\nSpeaker: Dr. David Sterratt, who is a Lecturer and the Deputy Director of Teaching (Operations) in the University of Edinburgh School of Informatics\n\nTitle: What I learned at the UK Conference on Teaching Statistics 2025, and the talk I gave there: Assessment of Critical Evaluation in the age of LLMs\n\nAbstract: Abstract\n\nWe hope to see you at the Teaching Hour !\n\nBest regards,\nCSEG Website System	\N	\N	\N	2026-03-02 09:00:00	\N	t	f	t	\N	\N	Abstract\n	t	in-person event	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
